'''Matheus Luiz Nunes'''  (born 27 August 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] or [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. Initially only a midfielder, he switched to right-back in the [[2024–25 Manchester City F.C. season|2024–25 season]].

Nunes started his career with [[G.D.U. Ericeirense|Ericeirense]], before moving to [[LigaPro]] side [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]]. During his time with the club, Nunes played mostly in the [[reserve team]], before moving to [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Sporting CP]] in January 2019. With Sporting, Nunes won a [[Primeira Liga]] title and back-to-back [[Taça da Liga|Taças da Liga]] in [[2020–21 Taça da Liga|2021]] and [[2021–22 Taça da Liga|2022]], while being part of the squad that won a [[Double (association football)|double]] in 2021. In August, Nunes signed with [[Premier League]] side [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for a club-record transfer worth €45&nbsp;million (£38&nbsp;million), before moving to fellow Premier League side Manchester City the following season.

Born in Brazil, Nunes moved to Portugal at 12 years old. He opted to play for the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]], and made his senior international debut in 2021, representing the side at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
[[File:Matheus Nunes (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Nunes training with [[Sporting CP]] in 2021]]

===Early career===
Nunes was born in [[Rio de Janeiro]]. After his father left his family,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Matheus Nunes dedica título à mãe: "Faço tudo por ela. Nunca soube o que era ter um pai" |trans-title=Matheus Nunes dedicates title to his mother: ″I do everything for her. I never knew what is like to have a father″ |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/matheus-nunes-dedica-titulo-a-mae-faco-tudo-por-ela-nunca-soube-o-que-era-ter-um-pai-13760700.html |access-date=17 October 2022 |website=ojogo.pt |language=pt-PT}}</ref> Nunes moved to [[Ericeira]], [[Lisbon District]] at the age of 12 with his mother and his English stepfather.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2056454/matheus-nunes-explica-bom-dominio-do-ingles-com-raizes-familiares|title=Matheus Nunes explica bom domínio do inglês com raízes familiares|trans-title=Matheus Nunes explains his good command of English with his roots|publisher=Notícias ao Minuto|language=pt|date=18 August 2022|access-date=7 June 2023}}</ref> He started playing football with local side [[G.D.U. Ericeirense|Ericeirense]] in the 6th division, and to help his family he also worked at his godfather's bakery for a short period while playing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/selecao-brasileira/noticia/na-mira-de-portugal-quem-e-matheus-nunes-foi-padeiro-e-atleta-no-inicio-da-carreira-em-lisboa.ghtml|title=Quem é Matheus Nunes, a novidade de Tite que estava na mira de Portugal e foi padeiro no início da carreira|trans-title=Who is Matheus Nunes, Tite's new face who was poised for Portugal and was a baker at the beginning of his career|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|Globo Esporte]]|first1=Bruno|last1=Cassucci|first2=Raphael|last2=Zarko|language=pt|date=27 August 2021|access-date=28 August 2021}}</ref>

Nunes made his senior debut for Ericeirense during the 2015–16 season, in the [[Lisbon Football Association]]. He started the 2017 pre-season on trial at [[Clube Oriental de Lisboa|Oriental]], but was not signed due to a thigh injury, and subsequently returned to his first club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/perfil/historia/de-chumbado-no-benfica-a-mina-de-ouro-de-varandas-quem-e-matheus-nunes|title=De chumbado no Benfica a mina de ouro de Varandas: quem é Matheus Nunes?|trans-title=From not making the cut at Benfica to Varandas gold mine: who is Matheus Nunes?|publisher=Mais Futebol|first=Adérito|last=Esteves|language=pt|date=2 February 2021|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref>

===Estoril===
Nunes signed with [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] in the summer of 2018. He made his debut in the [[LigaPro]] on 14 October in a 2–2 draw against [[Varzim S.C.|Varzim]], starting but leaving injured shortly before the end of the first half.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/varzim/detalhe/estoril-varzim-2-2-empate-caseiro-chegou-nos-descontos?ref=Pesquisa_Destaques|title=Estoril-Varzim, 2–2: Empate caseiro chegou nos descontos|trans-title=Estoril-Varzim, 2–2: Home draw arrived in injury time|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=14 October 2018|access-date=19 April 2021|archive-date=22 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422025309/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/varzim/detalhe/estoril-varzim-2-2-empate-caseiro-chegou-nos-descontos?ref=Pesquisa_Destaques|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/jogos-em-direto/live/72428|title=Estoril 2–2 Varzim|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=14 October 2018|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref> During most of his spell, he was associated to the [[reserve team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bolanarede.pt/rubricas/olheirobnr/olheiro-bnr-matheus-nunes-2/|title=Olheiro BnR {{!}} Matheus Nunes|trans-title=BnR scout {{!}} Matheus Nunes|publisher=Bola Na Rede|first=Tiago|last=Silva|language=pt|date=24 May 2020|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
On 29 January 2019, Nunes joined [[Sporting CP]] of the [[Primeira Liga]] on a five-and-a-half-year contract for a €500,000 fee for half of his economic rights, and a €45&nbsp;million [[buyout clause]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-ja-assinou|title=Matheus Nunes já assinou pelo Sporting|trans-title=Matheus Nunes has already signed for Sporting|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=29 January 2019|access-date=19 April 2021|archive-date=22 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422182522/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-ja-assinou|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1483319/sporting-pode-exercer-opcao-por-matheus-nunes-ate-janeiro|title="Sporting pode exercer opção por Matheus Nunes até janeiro"|trans-title="Sporting may exercise option on Matheus Nunes until January"|publisher=Notícias ao Minuto|language=pt|date=20 May 2020|access-date=4 June 2020}}</ref> His performances against Sporting for Estoril in the [[Taça da Liga]] group stage in the [[2018–19 Taça da Liga|2018–19]] season was noted by Sporting scouting team, who decided to sign him.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Amaral Santos |first1=Francisco |title=Dos elogios de Pep ao reencontro especial. A 'explosão' de Matheus Nunes|trans-title=From praise from Pep to special meeting. The 'explosion' of Matheus Nunes |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1935448/dos-elogios-de-pep-ao-reencontro-especial-a-exploso-de-matheus-nunes |access-date=29 March 2022 |publisher=Notícias ao Minuto |date=18 February 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

After playing for the club's under-23 team, Nunes received his first call-up to the first team by manager [[Ruben Amorim]] on 4 June 2020, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the 2–2 draw at [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] in the Primeira Liga.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/liveblogs/v-guimaraes-sporting-a-segunda-estreia-de-amorim-com-duas-estreias-quaresma-e-matheus-sao-titulares/|title=Sporting esteve duas vezes em vantagem mas não foi além do empate em Guimarães (2–2) – como aconteceu|trans-title=Sporting were ahead twice but could only draw in Guimarães (2–2) – how it happened|newspaper=[[Observador]]|first=Bruno|last=Roseiro|language=pt|date=4 June 2020|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref> On 23 October, he agreed to a contract extension by a further year, increasing his [[buyout clause]] from €45&nbsp;million to €60&nbsp;million, with the club deciding to pay Estoril €450,000 for the other half of his economic rights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Oficial: Matheus Nunes renova com o Sporting até 2025 |trans-title=Official: Matheus Nunes renews with Sporting until 2025 |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/oficial-matheus-nunes-renova-com-o-sporting-ate-2025 |access-date=29 March 2022 |work=Record |date=27 October 2020 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=25 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220325015451/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/oficial-matheus-nunes-renova-com-o-sporting-ate-2025 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Matheus Nunes é leão a 100%: notícia Record oficializada |trans-title=Matheus Nunes is 100% a Lion: Record news confirmed |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-e-leao-a-100-noticia-record-oficializada |access-date=29 March 2022 |work=Record |date=18 February 2021 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=25 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220325015454/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-e-leao-a-100-noticia-record-oficializada |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Nunes scored his first goal in the Portuguese top division on 2 January 2021, closing the 2–0 home victory over [[S.C. Braga|Braga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/sporting-sp-braga-feddal-e-nuno-santos-de-volta-nos-leoes-13189290.html|title=Sporting 2–0 Sp. Braga. Leão imbatível abate minhotos|trans-title=Sporting 2–0 Sp. Braga. Unstoppable Lion downs men from Minho|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|first=António Pedro|last=Pereira|language=pt|date=2 January 2021|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref> His second came the following 1 February, in [[Last-minute goal|injury time]] to help the hosts defeat [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] 1–0 in the [[Lisbon derby]], being named man of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/1949-matheus-nunes-the-hero-in-sporting-s-late-smash-and-grab-versus-rivals-benfica|title=Matheus Nunes the hero in Sporting's late smash-and-grab versus rivals Benfica|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Patrick|last=Ribeiro|date=1 February 2021|access-date=19 April 2021}}</ref> Following the departure of [[João Mário (footballer, born January 1993)|João Mário]], he earned a permanent place in the starting eleven, and on 15 September, on in his [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] debut, he provided an assist for [[Paulinho (footballer, born November 1992)|Paulinho]] in a 5–1 away defeat to [[A.F.C. Ajax|Ajax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58577414|title=Sporting Lisbon 1–5 Ajax|website=[[BBC Sport]]|date=15 September 2021|access-date=17 September 2021}}</ref> After helping Sporting on a run of six consecutive league wins, including the [[Lisbon derby]] against Benfica, where provided an assist and scored a goal in a 3–1 away victory, Nunes was named the league's Midfielder of the Month for the months of October and November.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1892237/matheus-nunes-vence-prmio-de-melhor-mdio-do-ms|title=Matheus Nunes vence prémio de melhor médio do mês|trans-title=Matheus Nunes wins best midfielder of the montha ward|publisher=Notícias ao Minuto|date=14 December 2021|access-date=25 March 2022|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

On 15 February 2022, in the first leg of the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|round of 16 tie of the Champions League]], despite his team 5–0 home loss to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Pep Guardiola]], who was impressed by the calibre of Nunes' performances, praised him as "one of the best players in the world".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://expresso.pt/expresso/2022-02-16-guardiola-diz-que-matheus-nunes-e-um-dos-melhores-do-mundo-e-que-resultado-com-o-sporting-nao-espelha-a-diferenca-entre-as-equipas|title=Guardiola diz que "Matheus Nunes é um dos melhores do mundo" e que resultado com o Sporting "não espelha a diferença entre as equipas"|trans-title=Guardiola says that "Matheus Nunes is one of the world's best" and that the result against Sporting "does not reflect the difference between the teams|work=[[Expresso (newspaper)|Expresso]]|language=Portuguese|date=16 February 2022|access-date=29 March 2022}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
[[File:Matheus Nunes, WolvesvManCitySeptember2022 2 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=1.00|right|Nunes playing for [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in 2022|263x263px]]

On 17 August 2022, Nunes signed a five-year contract with English [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] for a club-record transfer worth €45&nbsp;million (£38&nbsp;million), surpassing the former record signing compatriot [[Fábio Silva (footballer, born 2002)|Fábio Silva]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Wolves complete record Nunes move |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20220817-wolves-complete-record-nunes-move/ |access-date=17 August 2022 |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers FC |date=17 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62586975|title=Matheus Nunes: Wolves sign Portugal midfielder for club record £38m fee|website=BBC Sport|date=18 August 2022}}</ref>

Nunes made his Wolves debut three days later, as a starter in a 1–0 defeat against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] at the [[Tottenham Hotspur Stadium]] in the Premier League on 20 August 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tottenham Hotspur 1–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Kane's 250th Tottenham goal takes them top|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62529371|website=BBC Sport|last=Sutcliffe|first=Steve|date=20 August 2022|access-date=20 August 2022}}</ref> Nunes made his home Premier League debut in a 1–1 draw with [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] at Molineux on 28 August 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62621480|title=Wolves 1–1 Newcastle Utd: Allan Saint-Maximin volley earns Newcastle a point|website=BBC Sport|first=Simon|last=Stone|date=28 August 2022}}</ref> Nunes scored his first goal for Wolves in their 1–0 home win against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 8 April 2023.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Summerscales |first=Robert |date=8 April 2023 |title=Matheus Nunes Scores First Goal For Wolves With Spectacular Thunderbolt Against Chelsea |work=[[FanNation]] |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/video/matheus-nunes-scores-superb-goal-for-wolves-against-chelsea |access-date=8 April 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65145676|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 1–0 Chelsea: Frank Lampard's first game as interim boss ends in defeat |first=Neil|last=Johnston|website=BBC Sport|date=8 April 2023|access-date=14 April 2023}}</ref>

During the early stages of the [[2023–24 Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. season|2023–24 season]], Nunes began a dispute with Wolves over his desire to leave the club after they had rejected a transfer bid for him worth £47&nbsp;million from [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66604463|title=Matheus Nunes: Wolves reject Man City's £47m offer for Portugal midfielder |first=Simon|last=Stone|website=BBC Sport|date=24 August 2023|access-date=29 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/24/wolves-reject-opening-47m-manchester-city-bid-for-matheus-nunes |title=Transfer roundup: Wolves reject £47m Manchester City bid for Matheus Nunes |first=Ben |last=Fisher|date= 24 August 2023 |work=The Guardian }}</ref> Nunes failed to turn up for training with the club, without the permission of manager [[Gary O'Neil]] for two consecutive days in a bid to secure a move away from the club, and was subsequently fined.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66642143|title=Matheus Nunes: Wolves midfielder to be fined after missing training |first=Simon|last=Stone|website=BBC Sport|date=28 August 2023|access-date=29 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/28/matheus-nunes-goes-on-strike-in-attempt-to-seal-manchester-city-move |title=Matheus Nunes goes on strike in attempt to seal Manchester City move |first=Ben |last=Fisher|date= 28 August 2023 |work=The Guardian }}</ref>

===Manchester City===
On 30 August 2023, it was reported that a £53&nbsp;million bid from Manchester City with no additional add-ons had been agreed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66662060|title=Matheus Nunes to Man City: Premier League champions agree £53m deal to sign Wolves midfielder |first=Simon|last=Stone|website=BBC Sport|date=31 August 2023|access-date=31 August 2023}}</ref> The transfer was confirmed on 1 September 2023. The Portuguese international signed a five-year deal with the reigning European and English champions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/nunes-joins-manchester-city-63829155|title=City secure Nunes signature|publisher=Manchester City F.C.|date=1 September 2023|access-date=1 September 2023}}</ref>

Nunes made his Manchester City debut on 16 September, coming off the bench to replace [[Phil Foden]] on the 67th minute of a 3–1 league victory away at [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Meyers |first=Billy |date=17 September 2023 |title=Manchester City fans react to Matheus Nunes debut after £53m move from Wolves |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/manchester-city-fans-react-to-matheus-nunes-debut-after-53m-move-from-wolves/ |access-date=23 September 2023 |website=Manchester City News}}</ref> Three days later, he made his first start for the ''Citizens'', playing the full 90 minutes in a 3–1 home win over [[Red Star Belgrade]] in the UEFA Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |last=Marrett |first=Adam |date=21 September 2023 |title=Matheus Nunes makes an immediate impact in first start for City. |url=https://esteemedkompany.com/2023/09/21/matheus-nunes-makes-an-immediate-impact-in-first-start-for-manchester-city/ |access-date=23 September 2023 |website=Esteemed Kompany}}</ref> Four days later, Nunes made his first Premier League start for City, playing the full match in a 2–0 home victory over [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]], where he assisted [[Erling Haaland]] for the second goal.<ref>{{cite web |date=23 September 2023 |title=Ten-man Man City show silk and steel to extend Premier League lead |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20230923-ten-man-man-city-show-silk-and-steel-to-extend-premier-league-lead |access-date=23 September 2023 |publisher=France 24}}</ref> Nunes won his first trophy at City on 22 December, as the team beat [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]] 4–0, with Nunes assisting [[Julian Álvarez]]'s winning goal in the [[2023 FIFA Club World Cup final]].<ref name="2023ClubWorldCupFinal">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67795653 |title=Manchester City 4–0 Fluminense |website=BBC Sport |date=22 December 2023 |access-date=22 December 2023}}</ref>

Nunes scored his first City goal on 24 September 2024 in the [[EFL Cup]], scoring the decisive goal in a 2–1 home win over [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the [[2024–25 EFL Cup#Third round|third round]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/czegp16denyt |title=Manchester City 2–1 Watford: Jeremy Doku and Matheus Nunes on target in Carabao Cup tie |website=BBC Sport |date=24 September 2024 |access-date=26 September 2024}}</ref> He scored his first [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal on 23 October against [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] with a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty]], while also recording two assists in a 5–0 home win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cgryenkew5kt |title=Manchester City 5–0 Sparta Prague: Erling Haaland's brilliant goal helps seal win in Champions League |website=BBC Sport |date=23 October 2024 |access-date=23 October 2024}}</ref> On 22 April 2025, Nunes scored his first Premier League goal, a 94th minute winner, in a 2–1 home victory over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ckg2420n65kt |title=Manchester City 2–1 Aston Villa |website=BBC Sport |date=22 April 2025 |access-date=22 April 2025}}</ref>

On 27 September 2025, Nunes scored his first goal of the [[2025–26 Manchester City F.C. season|2025–26 season]] in a 5–1 home victory over [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in the league.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-burnley-premier-league-match-report-1-63894574 |title=Late Haaland brace rounds off five-star victory over Burnley |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=27 September 2025 |access-date=27 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 8 August 2021, after living in the country for ten years, Nunes received his [[Portuguese passport]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-disponivel-para-representar-portugal-uma-decada-para-o-sonho|title=Matheus Nunes disponível para representar Portugal: uma década para o sonho|trans-title=Matheus Nunes available to play for Portugal: a decade for the dream|newspaper=Record|first1=João|last1=Soares Ribeiro|first2=Ricardo|last2=Granada|language=pt|date=8 August 2021|access-date=28 August 2021|archive-date=27 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221127171210/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/matheus-nunes-disponivel-para-representar-portugal-uma-decada-para-o-sonho|url-status=dead}}</ref> Later that month, on his 23rd birthday, he was called up by [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] manager [[Tite (football manager)|Tite]] as one of nine replacements for the players based in the United Kingdom, for three [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|qualifiers]] against [[Chile national football team|Chile]], [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] and [[Peru national football team|Peru]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/selecao-brasileira-convoca-nove-jogadores-para-a-data-fifa-de-setembro|title=Seleção brasileira convoca nove jogadores para a data FIFA de setembro|trans-title=Brazil national team call up nine players for FIFA schedules in September|publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]]|language=pt|date=27 August 2021|access-date=28 August 2021}}</ref> He refused the call, as he would have had to quarantine on return due not having the complete [[COVID-19 vaccination]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Seleção brasileira: Tite revela conversa com Matheus Nunes e diz por que jogador não se apresentou |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/artigo/_/id/9141561/selecao-brasileira-tite-revela-conversa-com-matheus-nunes-e-diz-por-que-jogador-nao-se-apresentou |access-date=29 March 2022 |publisher=[[ESPN Brasil]] |date=1 September 2021 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> Ultimately, Nunes decided not to represent his country of birth, after he was contacted by [[Portugal national football team|Portugal's national team]] manager [[Fernando Santos (footballer, born 1954)|Fernando Santos]], who convinced him to represent [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tntsports.com.br/futebolbrasileiro/Matheus-Nunes-decide-nao-se-apresentar-a-selecao-brasileira-20210827-0027.html|title=Matheus Nunes decide não se apresentar à seleção brasileira|trans-title=Matheus Nunes decides against reporting to the Brazilian national team|publisher=[[TNT Sports (Argentina)|TNT Sports]]|language=pt|date=27 August 2021|access-date=30 September 2021}}</ref>

Nunes was called by Santos on 30 September 2021 for World Cup [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifiers]] against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] and a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] with [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/portugal/selecao-nacional/selecao-a-lista-de-convocados-de-fernando-santos|title=Seleção: a lista de convocados de Fernando Santos|trans-title=National team: Fernando Santos' squad selection|publisher=Mais Futebol|first=Ricardo|last=Gouveia|language=pt|date=30 September 2021|access-date=30 September 2021}}</ref> He won his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] on 9 October, starting the 3–0 friendly win over Qatar in the [[Algarve]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/2287-portugal-3-0-qatar-matheus-nunes-rafael-leao-make-their-selecao-debuts|title=Portugal 3–0 Qatar – Diogo Costa, Matheus Nunes & Rafael Leão make their Seleção debuts|publisher=PortuGOAL|date=9 October 2021|accessdate=10 October 2021}}</ref> He scored his first international goal the following 22 March in a 3–1 home win over [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in the semi-finals of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|qualification play-offs]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Otavio, Jota, Nunes and a penalty miss send Portugal through |url=https://www.marca.com/en/world-cup/2022/03/24/623ce7ffe2704e42bb8b4601.html |access-date=29 March 2022 |work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=24 March 2022}}</ref>

In October, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/rumor-portugal-reportedly-announce-provisional-55-man-squad-2022-fifa-world-cup-liverpool-star-receives-surprise-call|title=Portugal reportedly name provisional 55-man squad for 2022 FIFA World Cup; Liverpool star receives surprise call up|publisher=Sportskeeda|first=Dakir Mohammed|last=Thanveer|date=25 October 2022|access-date=9 November 2022}}</ref> being included in the final 26-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|title=Os 26 convocados de Portugal: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio e Matheus Nunes chamados|trans-title=Portugal select 26: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio and Matheus Nunes called|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=10 November 2022|access-date=10 November 2022}}</ref>

On 3 June 2024, he was named in the squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]], as a replacement to the injured [[Otávio (footballer, born 1995)|Otávio]],<ref>{{cite news |date=3 June 2024 |title=Matheus Nunes convocado para o Euro 2024 |trans-title=Matheus Nunes called up for Euro 2024 |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45273 |language=pt |publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |access-date=3 June 2024}}</ref> where Portugal was eliminated from the tournament by [[France national football team|France]] in the quarter-finals, after losing 5–3 in a [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Emma|last=Sanders|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Nunes is usually deployed in double pivot in [[Formation (association football)|3–4–3]] formation, operating as a number 8 looking to get forward and contribute to the attack and also has a good passing range, as he can make different types of passes whether he is looking to switch the play or try and break lines with penetrative passes, or  passes that split the opposition backline, which he is highly effective at. He also has the ability to carry the ball and make progressive runs, using a combination of speed and strength to make these runs, while also displaying good technique on the ball. Nunes also possesses good anticipation and reading of the game, which allows him to make effective interceptions and challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/competitions/primeira-liga/primeira-liga-2021-22-matheus-nunes-scout-report-tactical-analysis-analysis|title=Matheus Nunes 2021/22: The Portuguese midfielder impressing in the Primeira Liga – Scout Report|date=24 December 2021 }}</ref>

